The White House Press Secretary, Josh Earnest, held a press briefing where he addressed various topics. He discussed President Obama's fundraisers in New York City, the meeting between President Obama and Prime Minister Modi of India, the Paris climate agreement, and the ongoing Democratic primary race between Hillary Clinton and Bernie Sanders. Earnest also commented on the controversial sentencing in the Stanford sexual assault case and the minimum wage increase in Washington D.C. He concluded by highlighting the importance of the U.S.-India relationship and the progress made in terms of civil rights and gender equality.